      <altformavail id="aspace_d5b488cb2cf9aba982e53c47bdfe942a">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm (2,802 frames on 4 reels, 35mm.) from Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library, at cost. <num>Order no. HM141.</num>
         </p>  
      </altformavail>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_93da3fe9b72815088ae2d803bc9ed946">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Asa Fitch Papers consist of fifty items. Twenty-one of these are diaries kept by Asa Fitch from 1821 through 1879 in various places in New York State and elsewhere. Notations for several years are lacking. Six volumes, 1821-1828, were lettered A through G, with B missing. To the remaining fifteen volumes numbers have arbitrarily been assigned, although entries are not always consecutive by date.</p>
         <p>The remainder of the collection is made up of Fitch family genealogical material copied from the notes of the father of Abbie M. (Fitch) Andrews (1840-) and notes taken from her own research.</p>
         <p>A detailed description of the contents of the diaries and other papers follows.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0bb87f29304548bab359ff598c41e236">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Practiced medicine, 1831-1838; studied economic entomology and agriculture, and began publishing articles on the subject in 1845; in 1854 appointed state entomologist of New York, remaining until 1871.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_5185a39dd1a30ddec2a32b23990515a5">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm. Patrons must use FILM HM 141 instead of the originals.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
